cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with a computer vision problem of blind deconvolution and proposes a solution using generative networks and neural optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The paper also deals with image processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks for optimization, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category.
